page.title: 01High Country Gunthorpe
page.content: Generously wooded undulating arable and featuring one of the highest points in Norfolk and three pretty villages. Traditional country estates preserving good sporting and amenity with pheasant shooting and sizeable predominantly arable farms. Some sheep, fattening cattle on lower meadows and one dairy farm. Very little modern development but old cottages modernished some for holiday/weekend use. Four kilometres squares contain no buildings. A large area of farmland owned by an insurance company pension fund including a small part afforested.
